Pharyngoconjunctival fever is a viral infection that affects the throat and eyes, causing symptoms such as fever, sore throat, and redness in the eyes. The global market for pharyngoconjunctival fever can be segmented based on treatment type, distribution channel, and region. In terms of treatment type, the market is categorized into antipyretics, analgesics, antiviral drugs, and others. Antipyretics and analgesics are commonly used to manage symptoms such as fever and sore throat, while antiviral drugs may be prescribed in severe cases. Regarding distribution channels, pharyngoconjunctival fever treatments are typically available in hospital pharmacies, retail pharmacies, and online pharmacies. Geographically, the market is divided into North America, Europe, Asia-Pacific, Latin America, and the Middle East and Africa.

